bug.short_desc: Gvim fails to properly render after Openbox desktop switch
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem:
Using Fedora 24, Openbox 3.6.1 and vim-* 2:8.0.124-2.fc24, gvim fails to properly render if you switch to a different Openbox desktop and then switch back. Much of the text is missing. If you refresh with Control-L, it restores.
Downgrading to:
vim-X11.x86_64 2:7.4.1718-1.fc24 vim-common.x86_64 2:7.4.1718-1.fc24 vim-enhanced.x86_64 2:7.4.1718-1.fc24 vim-filesystem.x86_64 2:7.4.1718-1.fc24 vim-minimal.x86_64 2:7.4.1718-1.fc2
solved the issue for me.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
vim-X11.x86_64 2:8.0.124-2.fc24 @updates vim-common.x86_64 2:8.0.124-2.fc24 @updates vim-enhanced.x86_64 2:8.0.124-2.fc24 @updates vim-filesystem.x86_64 2:8.0.124-2.fc24 @updates vim-minimal.x86_64 2:8.0.124-2.fc24 @updates
How reproducible:
100%
Steps to Reproduce: 1. using Openbox, open gvim, & look at a file with some text 2. switch to another desktop 3. switch back
Actual results:
Expected results:
Additional info:

Hi Ross,
I tried to reproduce this issue on Fedora rawhide with vim-8.0-133 and it seems ok. Would you mind trying the newest version of vim, if it helps?
Seems OK == no problem with rendering.

I've been able to reproduce this with freshly installed VMs with both Fedora 24 and Fedora 25. The reproduction steps are the same for both:
clean install of Fedora 24/25 Workstation in a QEMU/KVM VM dnf update -y dnf install gvim openbox mkdir /root/.config/openbox copy /etc/xdg/openbox/* /root/.config/openbox reboot with latest kernel & so openbox shows up in gdm menu log into openbox as root open /root/anaconda-ks.cfg in gvim switch to desktop 2 with alt-F2, and back with alt-F1 the lines where the desktop switcher popup appeared, the text is garbled [ this can be seen with the popup in attached Screenshot 1, and after the popup fades in Screenshot 2]
Hit Control-L to refresh the gvim display, and the text is restored [Screenshot 3]
Thanks Ross, I was able to reproduce it with your instructions. I will look into it, if it is openbox or vim issue.
This issue is caused by commit, in which gtk3 was set to use instead of gtk2. If problem is caused by wrong usage of GTK3 API in vim or by bug in GTK3, I will investigate.

Hi Ross,
I found patch in vim-dev mailing list, which solves the issue. There are rpms https://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/taskinfo?taskID=17993508 .
vim-8.0.347-2.fc25 has been submitted as an update to Fedora 25. https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/FEDORA-2017-e75b8b057b

I can verify that the issue appears to be fixed in vim-8.0-347-2.fc25
Thanks!
